{{DISPLAYTITLE:<span style="opacity: 0">Moonlantern</span>}}
{{Background|file=Void.png}}
<center><span style="background:linear-gradient(90deg,#8f9cff,#4350ac,#8f9cff); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent; font-family:'Roboto Mono'; text-shadow: #8f9cff 0em 0em 0.5em; font-size: 80px">Object 26:<br> Moonlantern</span>
[[File:Moonlantern.png|center|thumb|170px]]
<div style="background: #3038f7; padding: 5px; box-shadow: 0px 5px 10px rgba(48, 56, 247); border-radius: 8px">
<div style="background: #020309; border: 3px solid #8f9cff; border-image: #8f9cff) 1 round; no-repeat; border-radius: 19px; padding: 20px; color: white;">
<center>
'''Moonlanterns''' are advanced types of flashlights that use '''Glowing Moonstone''' as a light source. Most of them have 5 beacons, one at the center and the other 2 at the sides. Though sometimes it is possible to find standard flashlight structures with just one. It emits a soft bluish light, and its most known for possessing the unique ability to highlight many environmental clues, such as objects, exits, and sometimes even entities (doesn't apply to dark-based entities).<br>
<center><span style="font-size: 40px">Usage</span>
{{Underline|8f9cff}}
'''Moonlanterns '''are very useful and are always great to have if you're exploring any levels, especially dark ones. Working in a way similar to [[Object 25|Flashies]], they can highlight many important items such as [[Object 1|Almond Water]], [[Object 13|Luck Clovers]] and [[Object 6|Moth Jelly]]. They can also highlight potential exits and entities, making them a good asset when it comes to escaping levels safely and harvesting resources. While this is all good, Moonlanterns cannot highlight entities that thrive in the dark, making the user still susceptible to threats such as [[Entity 3|Smilers]].

Despite more advanced Moonlanterns having additional beacons, this doesn't mean Moonlanterns can be used as a casual light source and should only be used if there are no other alternatives for a light source. This is because of how rare '''Glowing Moonstones''' are and how quick they can expire if used significantly. Moonlanterns are very rare to find, but they can be found in big colonies or outposts in some [[:Category:Space|spatial levels]], and very rarely inside chests within Luna Villages in [[Level 700]].

A more simple way of making a moonlantern is replacing a flashlight's bulb with Glowing Moonstone, though you'd still have to find it, and as of now, they're only known to be in [[Level 700]].
<center><span style="font-size: 40px">History</span>
{{Underline|8f9cff}}
'''Moonlanterns''' were discovered when a group of M.E.G. specialists sent for resource extraction found a lamp fueled by Glowing Moonstone inside one of the buildings of a Deserted Village. This lamp was later taken to a M.E.G. base and was studied and replicated. It would at first be only for M.E.G. affiliates until [[Phenomenon 12|The Flicker]], when, due to the abundance of darkness, it became widespread across The Backrooms. 

After The Flicker, due to more widespread awareness about the utility of this object, it continued to be used in many advanced groups and colonies.
<center><span style="font-size: 40px">Disadvantages</span>
{{Underline|8f9cff}}
While Moonlanterns are very effective, they also have noticeable disadvantages: Having a significantly lower battery duration than average flashlights and a lack of accessibility to Glowing Moonstone, makes them inconvenient to use for long periods of time and costly to make. Additionally, it is important to note '''Moonlanterns only work when its nighttime on when the lights are off in a level'''. This means Moonlanterns are instantly obsolete in any level with frequent light. When using Moonlanterns, the best solution is to not completely rely on them to scavenge or escape levels. It is also recommended to mindfully conserve a Moonlantern's power with at least 1-2 uses per level, as you don't know when you could need it the most. Again, due to their low fuel time, unless they're being used for their specific purpose, Moonlanterns are an unreliable common light source, and its best to simply use normal flashlights if you want to use them just to illuminate.
